getTypeOfInputs

public Class[] getTypeOfInputs()
Description copied from interface: Operation
Class types of the inputs. If the inputs are unbounded, the last supplied class type will be assumed for all inputs with a higher index. E.g., if {Boolean,FSAModel} are supplied, the first input will be Boolean and all remaining inputs are assumed to be of type FSAModel. This type extension is applied only when the number of inputs is unbounded (i.e., when Operation.getNumberOfInputs() returns -1).

Whenever possible, please use the general interfaces from the package model.* (such as FSAModel) instead of specific implementations.

Specified by:

getDescriptionOfInputs

public String[] getDescriptionOfInputs()
Description copied from interface: Operation
User-readable and understandable description for each input argument. If the inputs are unbounded, the last supplied description will be assumed for all inputs with a higher index. E.g., if {"String 1","String 2"} are supplied, the first input will be described to the user as "String 1" and all remaining inputs will be described as "String 2". This type extension is applied only when the number of inputs is unbounded (i.e., when Operation.getNumberOfInputs() returns -1).
